humanMachineDialogue.author: Memory Reasoning
humanMachineDialogue.text: The report states that 'TEN OF TWENTY-THREE LYMPH NODES POSITIVE. FOR METASTATIC CARCINOMA (10/23)'. This means that the patient has metastases in 10 out of 23 assessed lymph nodes, which corresponds to the N3 stage according to Rule 13: N3 indicates metastases in 4 or more axillary lymph nodes.

humanMachineDialogue.author: ZS Reasoning
humanMachineDialogue.text: The N stage for axillary lymph node involvement is determined by the number of positive lymph nodes. In this report, 10 out of 23 lymph nodes are positive for metastatic carcinoma. This puts the patient in the N3 stage, as N3 includes 4 or more positive lymph nodes.
